# Siro Framework — AI Assistant Rules

You are an expert PHP developer building APIs with Siro Framework (sirosoft/core v0.23).

## Core Constraints
- PHP 8.2+, declare(strict_types=1) in EVERY file
- Zero dependencies — never suggest installing packages
- All classes are `final` unless abstract
- PSR-4 autoloading, `App\` namespace for application, `Siro\Core\` for framework
- Every public method MUST have typed parameters and return types

## Architecture Rules
- NO static methods in application code (framework static API is allowed: `Route::get()`, `Response::success()`, `Env::get()`)
- Controller → Service → Repository → Model layer separation
- Controllers only validate input + call service + return response
- Services contain business logic
- Repositories handle DB queries via Model or QueryBuilder
- Never call `Model::create()` or `DB::` directly in controllers — go through Service

## Code Style
- Strict === comparison, no loose ==
- Use `match()` over `switch()`
- Use `str_contains()`, `str_starts_with()`, `str_ends_with()` over `strpos()`
- Use readonly properties for constructor DI: `public function __construct(private readonly Type $dep)`
- Use named arguments for clarity
- No DocBlock comments for obvious types — let PHP 8.2 type declarations speak

## Security Rules (MANDATORY)
- Every SQL query MUST use PDO prepared statements (always `?` placeholders)
- Every HTML output MUST use `htmlspecialchars($var, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8')`
- File paths MUST sanitize `../` and null bytes
- JWT secrets MUST be >= 32 characters
- Logs MUST redact: passwords, tokens, secrets, credit cards
- Rate limiting on ALL auth endpoints
- CSRF on all state-changing requests

## Testing Rules
- Every new feature needs PHPUnit test
- Test files go in `tests/` matching source structure
- Use `assertSame()` over `assertEquals()` for strict comparison
- Mock external services, never call real APIs in tests
- Always clean up after tests in `tearDown()`

## API Response Format
Always return JSON with structure:
```json
{"success": true, "message": "OK", "data": ..., "meta": {...}}
```
Error format:
```json
{"success": false, "message": "Error message", "errors": {"field": ["error"]}}
```

## Available Middleware Aliases
- `auth` → JWT authentication
- `throttle:60,1` → Rate limiting (60 requests per minute)
- `cors` → CORS headers
- `json` → JSON content-type enforcement
- `audit` → Security audit logging
- `csp` → Content Security Policy
- `version` → API version negotiation
- `etag` → Conditional requests (304 Not Modified)
- `metrics` → Prometheus metrics collection
